This paper proposes a technique for regression testing configurable systems, which involves exploring all dynamically reachable configurations from a test. This technique is specifically designed for handling two scenarios in the context of evolution, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses experimental results on a real-world configurable system (GCC), which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of different techniques, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
